description:
&lt;p&gt;We have band 5 opportunities to join our nursing team on 9 North Ward at The Royal Free London NHS Foundation Trust. We are offering band 5 nurses the opportunity to expand their knowledge and skills in the field of hepatology and liver transplant nursing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Royal Free London NHS Foundation Trust is a national centre leading on liver disease and liver transplantation, one of only six liver transplant centres in the UK, in addition we also provide care for gastroenterology patients within ward 9N.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have excellent communication skills, work well as part of our team and be dedicated to provide a high quality patient experience in line with the Royal Free care values. In return, we will provide you with robust local induction, one to one clinical supervision, teaching and study with our dedicated and supportive Clinical Practice Educator. You will have access to numerous study days including the preceptorship programme and continuous training opportunities with the support of practice development team. Further education is supported by the Trust offering courses/modules with our two link universities, Middlesex and Kings College.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We can offer assistance with accommodation, a wide range of benefits including on site leisure facilities, day nurseries and access to great transport system with easy access to airports and rail travel. We also offer Internal Transfer Scheme (after 9 months) and access to Career Clinics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At the Royal Free London NHS Foundation Trust, we believe in providing world-class medical treatment alongside an excellent patient experience. The Royal Free London Hospital has a world-class reputation for research and teaching. If you have the passion to provide kind, safe and excellent care we can offer you a great place to nurse and develop your career. We are focused on improving quality: for our patients, their carers/families and for our staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We support flexible working.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ward Manager, Achilleas Kiourkas achilleas.kiourkas@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Matron Liver, Hepatology &amp; HBP Caterina Falce on Bleep 712871(caterina.falce@nhs.net)&lt;/p&gt;
